The paper proposes a technique for real-time probabilistic scene modeling and mapping for co-robotic exploration in communication constrained environments. This involves the use of an underwater robot that learns an unsupervised scene model of the environment and communicates the spatial distribution of various high-level semantic scene constructs to a human operator. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Robotics (cs.RO), Computer Vision (cs.CV), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), or Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories.
